k
 n^{k+1}= O(1^k + 2^k + \cdots + n^k) 
1^k + 2^k +\cdots + n^k =O(n^{k+1})
(n+1)^k
n^{k+1}=O(1^k+2^k+\cdots+n^k)
n\to\infty
n\cdot n^k\geqslant\sum_{i=1}^ni^k\geqslant\sum_{i=1}^n\int_{i-1}^it^k\,\mathrm dt=\int_{0}^nt^k\,\mathrm dt=\frac{n^{k+1}}{k+1}.
 1^k+2^k+\cdots+n^k=\Theta(n^k).
\sum_{i=1}^n i^k \ge \sum_{i=\lfloor n/2 \rfloor }^n i^k \ge \frac{n-1}{ 2} \left( \frac{n-1}{ 2} \right)^k =\Omega(n^{k+1})
